1) Transparent data encryption:-
- Database data, log files, backup, all are encrypted.
- Data fetched is auto decrypted.
- Auto enabled for Azure SQL Database(Not for azure sql mgd instance)
- Use key provided by azure or own key in vault

2) Aazure SQL server - always encrypted:
- protect sensitive data
- Data protected at rest, when it is moved from the client and server and when data is in use.

3) Azure disk encryption:
- enable encyption of OS or data disks attached to VM
- For linux, use DM crypt for volume encryption
- For windowsVM, use bit locker.

4) Azure storage encryption:
- auto encrypt data at rest. Auto enabled for all storage accounts.
- use customer mgd key from kv svc or use customer-provided keys when perform ops on blob.

